.reverse -> cambia y lo deja alréves
poem.lines.to_a.reverse -> First, you turned the poem into a list using lines.to_a. The lines component decided the way the string should be split up, and then one of our "to" methods, to_a, converted those splits into an Array. (to_array.)
.join -> une en un string
.downcase -> imprime abajo hacía arriba
.delete -> elimina lo que está en la variable
books= {} -> crea un diccionario

categorias del diccionario -> 
    :splendid → a masterpiece.
    :quite_good → enjoyed, sure, yes.
    :mediocre → equal parts great and terrible.
    :quite_not_good → notably bad.
    :abysmal → steaming wreck.


